=== Application and expansion process ===
Discussions about allowing new countries to join the group were not widely talked about until the early 2020s. At that time, leaders and top diplomats from the member countries started to consider the possibility of expanding the group to include new members.<ref name="Silk Road Briefing">{{cite news |last=Devonshire-Ellis |first=Chris |date=9 November 2022 |title=The New Candidate Countries For BRICS Expansion |work=Silk Road Briefing |url=https://www.silkroadbriefing.com/news/2022/11/09/the-new-candidate-countries-for-brics-expansion/ |access-date=21 February 2023 |archive-date=17 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230117205632/https://www.silkroadbriefing.com/news/2022/11/09/the-new-candidate-countries-for-brics-expansion/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="BRICS Expansion Dialogue">{{cite news |date=20 May 2022 |title=Wang Yi Chairs Dialogue of Foreign Ministers between BRICS and Emerging Markets and Developing Countries |work=Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the People's Republic of China |url=https://www.fmprc.gov.cn/mfa_eng/topics_665678/kjgzbdfyyq/202205/t20220520_10690435.html |access-date=21 February 2023 |archive-date=15 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230415235040/https://www.fmprc.gov.cn/mfa_eng/topics_665678/kjgzbdfyyq/202205/t20220520_10690435.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Anadolu Agency">{{cite news |last=Teslova |first=Elena |date=8 November 2022 |title=At least a dozen countries interested in joining BRICS: Russian foreign minister |work=Anadolu Agency |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/russia-ukraine-war/at-least-a-dozen-countries-interested-in-joining-brics-russian-foreign-minister/2732749 |access-date=21 February 2023 |archive-date=16 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230116221958/https://www.aa.com.tr/en/russia-ukraine-war/at-least-a-dozen-countries-interested-in-joining-brics-russian-foreign-minister/2732749 |url-status=live }}</ref> While there is currently no formal application process to join BRICS, any hopeful government must receive the unanimous backing of all BRICS member states to receive an invitation.

